,"departure_arrival.checkin":"Checkin time","departure_arrival.checkout":"Checkout time","departure_arrival.on":"On block","departure_arrival.on_eta":"On block (ETA)","departure_arrival.eta":"ETA","departure_arrival.off_block":"ATD","departure_arrival.off":"Off block","departure_arrival.takeoff":"Takeoff","departure_arrival.landing":"Landing","departure_arrival.off_block_future":"Off > now","departure_arrival.departure_aircraft_info":"Fuel for departures reflect on the aircraft\'s current fuel, {aircraftLink} to change current fuel on the booked aircraft.","departure_arrival.departure_aircraft_info_no_access":"Fuel for departures reflect on the aircraft\'s current fuel, changes should be done by a maintenance administrator.","departure_arrival.departure_info":"<b>DEPARTURES</b><br/>Displays bookings which are within XX hours from ETD (Estimated Time of Departure). Bookings under departures can be in one of two stages (status) = Scheduled or Briefing.<br/><br/><b>Scheduled:</b> Flight is scheduled, but briefing not yet initiated.<br/><br/><b>Briefing:</b> Flight registrant* has initiated the briefing by clicking Proceed on the booking and entered the flight registration page.<br/><br/>DEPARTURE info (except \u2018status\u2019) is based on what has been booked. Changes must be done via Create Bookings.<br/><br/><i>*Flight registrant is the instructor, crew, or renter responsible for the flight registration.</i><br/><br/>","departure_arrival.arrival_info":"<b>ARRIVALS</b><br/>Displays aircraft which are in flight.<br/>Flights under arrivals can be in one of two stages (status) = Flight or Landed<br/><br/><b>Flight:</b> Flight registrant* has initiated the flight by clicking the action button Off block (OFF) or Takeoff (T/O) on the flight registration page.<br/><br/><b>Landed:</b> Flight registrant* has indicated a safe landing by clicking the action button Landing (LAN) on the flight registration page.<br/><br/>ARRIVAL info is based on the actions done by the flight registrant* live from the cockpit and/or the dispatcher live from the ground.<br/><br/><i>*Flight registrant is the instructor, crew, or renter responsible for the flight registration.</i><br/><br/>","departure_arrival.history_info":"<b>HISTORY</b><br/>Displays aircraft which has safely returned after a flight.<br/>Aircraft under history can be in one of two stages (status) = Debriefing or Completed.<br/><br/><b>Debriefing:</b> Flight registrant* has initiated the debriefing by clicking the action button On block (ON) on the flight registration page.<br/><br/><b>Completed:</b> Flight registrant* has completed the registration by clicking Submit on the flight registration page.<br/><br/>HISTORY info is based on the submitted registration done by the flight registrant*. Note that while in debriefing (shortly before the registration is submitted) only limited flight info is displayed. Once the registration is submitted all flight info will be displayed and the PIC of each flight will show in bold.<br><br><div><b>Movements:</b></div> <div><span class=\'fa fa-plane\'></span> Shows when and who changed the status from Briefing to Flight.</div> <div><span class=\'fa fa-comments\'></span> Shows when and who changed the status from Landed to Debriefing.</div> <div>NOTE: Converted checkins follow the checkin/out time that was registered.</div>  <br/><i>*Flight registrant is the instructor, crew, or renter responsible for the flight registration.</i><br/><br/>","departure_arrival.departure_booking_info":"Departures reflect on what was booked, changes should be done on the {bookingLink} page.","departure.arrival.help_center":"Read more about Departure Arrival in our help center {helpCenterLink}","departure.arrival.departure_booking_link":"Any other changes needed to departures should be done from the {bookingLink} page.","departure_arrival.departure_booking_info_no_access":"Departures reflect on what was booked, changes should be done by a booking administrator.","departure_arriv